      About this item

      • Colorful LED Lights: KANTUTOE TV LED lights strip features a remarkable 16 million colors mood light, capable of generating various color atmospheres for different settings. Whether it's your bedroom, gaming room, or home theater, this TV LED lights can consistently create unique scenes and ambiances tailored to your preferences.
      • Bluetooth App Control: LED Lights for TV can be connected to a mobile app via Bluetooth. Through the mobile app, you can not only control a wide range of lighting modes but also activate the music mode, allowing the lights to synchronize and change according to the rhythm of the music.
      • Sync with Music: KANTUTOE LED TV lights is different from ordinary TV lights strips. It has a built-in high-sensitivity microphone, and its color can change according to the change of the music. Let you enjoy the happiness brought by music more.
      • Multi-Application: LED for TV are suitable for most places such as living room, home theater, house and also for various holiday decorations such as Halloween, Christmas, etc. Extremely low heat 5V USB power supply makes the decoration safer.
      • Easy Installation: 16.4ft TV lights can illuminate every side of your TV. The mini receiver can be well hidden behind your TV. Unique stronger foam adhesive and clips ensure the RGB LED light bar is better fixed on your TV.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      • WINTERHALTER
        5.0 out of 5 stars Exactly what I wanted , fits TV as expected
        Reviewed in the United States on July 7, 2024
        Color: MulticolorSize: 16.4FT for 45"-75" TVVerified Purchase
        I can't think of anything bad to say about this light strip. There are plenty of brightness settings, lots of color choices and the lights power on and off when I turn my TV on and Off so I don't have to use the separate remote. With the 16.4 length option I had more than enough to cover the outer edge of my 65" TV. Since I am essentially using them for BIAS lighting I can't say I notice any flicker at all as I'm never looking directly at the light source.

        Installation is easy if you are familiar with the process. The adhesion is good, making 45 degree corners can be a little tricky if you've never used this type of light strip before , I highly recommend you get an idea of how you want to lay out the lighting before you start pulling back the tape that covers the adhesive, and then when you start sticking it on just pull the tape back as you go. That or get some plastic led strip clips and don't even pull off the tape or deal with the adhesive.

        I've had issues with other USB light strips not being able to reach their full brightness due to power limitations on the TV, but I can crank this one all the way up with no problem.

        I use my TV in a very dark space, and I find that for me personally the default blue setting at about 50% power really helps reduce eye strain without being a distraction. That said there is a lot of color customizing you can do if you're looking for a very specific color.

        The only thing worth mentioning is that whole these types of lights have a setting for White light, they really don't produce anything close to a natural white like from a light bulb, they also don't have any setting that looks like a true warm ambient light. That is no an issue with this product specifically, but with all similar light strip. So if you're looking for white , soft white, or a warm light look you need to look at a completely different type of product.

        The attached pictures show the lowest and highest brightness as well as how the strip fits the back of the TV.

The adhesion is good, making 45 degree corners can be a little tricky if you've never used this type of light strip before , I highly recommend you get an idea of how you want to lay out the lighting before you start pulling back the tape that covers the adhesive, and then when you start sticking it on just pull the tape back as you go. That or get some plastic led strip clips and don't even pull off the tape or deal with the adhesive.

        I've had issues with other USB light strips not being able to reach their full brightness due to power limitations on the TV, but I can crank this one all the way up with no problem.

        I use my TV in a very dark space, and I find that for me personally the default blue setting at about 50% power really helps reduce eye strain without being a distraction. That said there is a lot of color customizing you can do if you're looking for a very specific color.

        The only thing worth mentioning is that whole these types of lights have a setting for White light, they really don't produce anything close to a natural white like from a light bulb, they also don't have any setting that looks like a true warm ambient light. That is no an issue with this product specifically, but with all similar light strip. So if you're looking for white , soft white, or a warm light look you need to look at a completely different type of product.

        The attached pictures show the lowest and highest brightness as well as how the strip fits the back of the TV.

        3.0 out of 5 stars They work but...
        Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2024
        Color: MulticolorSize: 13.1FT for 32"-65" TVVerified Purchase
        First and foremost, these lights seem to work just fine. For me, the quality I was hoping for wasn't there but for how affordable they are, I could forgo that. The adhesive on them seems pretty sticky and they seem to stay in place on the back of my TV despite there being a texture. What I didn't care for was the backing for the adhesive being split between two pieces that were adhered to the LED strip - I had to pull back some of the adhesive that laid over the top of the backing of the next adhesive strip in order to pull the backing off the next piece. Next, I found it pretty difficult to round corners when I was applying it. The corners look terrible on the back of my TV...nobody will typically see that depending how you have your room and TV set up. That leads me to my next concern - these strips are white and most TVs are black. If your TV is placed like mine where you could get a small glimpse of the back, the white strips might stand out to you... that's just something to be aware of. To use these effectively, your TV should be up against a wall. Next, I found these need a USB port to plug into on the back of your TV so be aware you'll one available for these. I found the remote to be a bit touchy. It seems to need to be angled JUST right to actually connect to the lights. A big bonus is that there is an app you can use to control the lights instead. I find that way easier to use than the remote. Overall, I find the lights are a bit harsh when flashing between colors. There doesn't seem to be a way to set the lights so they gently go to and from the next color. It seems to have a strong, strobe-like effect so be aware!

        Overall, I would say these are a budget friendly option. They just aren't what I was hoping for in the quality department.
